		<Row Tag="LOC_TUTORIAL_PLAGUES_NAME">
			<Text>Plagues</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_TUTORIAL_PLAGUES_BODY">
			<Text>A Settlement is suffering from an Outbreak. Outbreaks cause Unrest, pillage Buildings and Improvements and damage Units in the affected tiles. While a settlement is Infected, it cannot grow and will create Migrants instead.[n]Major Outbreaks can spread and cause Minor Outbreaks in Connected settlements.[n]Outbreaks are more likely to occur in settlements that are densely populated, connected to road and trade networks or under siege.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_TUTORIAL_REVOLTS_NAME">
			<Text>Revolts</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_TUTORIAL_REVOLTS_BODY">
			<Text>The Settlement of [b]{1_CityName} [/b] is so unhappy they are considering Revolt. If they remain Unhappy they may petition to join another Civilization.[n]Consider changing your Policies or moving Resources to this settlement to improve their Happiness. If all else fails, Stationing a Commander here will help reduce the Unhappiness as well.</Text>
